  "body": "# Bug Report\r\n\r\nIn the chat screen of the removed contact, the `Add <CONTACT_NAME> to send a message` text overflows if the contact name is long.\r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/19339952/e2cc51d6-7aef-47c0-bb36-fd2cb130cc74\" width=\"300\" />\r\n\r\n\r\n### Expected behaviour\r\n\r\nThe text should not overflow.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n#### Prerequisites: Have at least one mutual contact\r\n\r\n1) Open Status\r\n2) Set/Update the nickname of the contact to the longest one\r\n3) Remove them from contacts\r\n4) Enter the chat of that removed user\r\n5) Check the text in the bottom drawer\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n\r\n- Status Version: nightly [06/08] \r\n- Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
